The paper focuses on deep learning and classification tasks, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a novel deep learning approach for one-shot classification also suggests a focus on machine learning and computer vision, making cs.LG and cs.CV the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper's emphasis on human cognitive behavior and memory could also suggest a connection to cs.AI and cs.NE, while the use of language to describe the approach could suggest a connection to cs.CL.
